File: SAA has been put under business rescue. JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways (SAA) business rescue plan will only be published at the end of March. The plan was expected to be out before next Friday. Business rescue practitioners have received permission from lenders and creditors for an extension. READ: SAA to get R16bn bailout In a statement, practitioners Siviwe Dongwana and Les Matuson say they're still in the process of finalising steps to implement the proposed restructuring option. Also, they need to consider the effect the plan will have on stakeholders, including the estimated return to creditors.